## 5. Repository

- Extends `JpaRepository<Entity, IdType>`.
- Soft-delete aware: **always** filter `isDeleted = false` in every query method.
- Use derived method names for simple conditions (≤ 3 conditions).
- Use `@Query` for complex conditions.

### Return type rules

| Situation | Repository returns |
|---|---|
| Single entity lookup | `Entity` / `Optional<Entity>` |
| List / paginated query | `List<Entity>` / `Page<Entity>` |
| JOIN across tables, partial fields | Interface Projection or DTO Projection (see below) |

**Default: Repository always returns Entity.** Only use Projection when a query JOINs multiple tables and mapping to a full entity is wasteful or not possible.

```java
public interface RoomRepository extends JpaRepository<Room, Long> {
    // Simple — derived method
    List<Room> findAllByIsDeletedFalse();
    Page<Room> findAllByIsDeletedFalse(Pageable pageable);
    Optional<Room> findByIdAndIsDeletedFalse(Long id);

    // Complex — @Query returning entity
    @Query("SELECT r FROM Room r WHERE r.status = :status AND r.isDeleted = false")
    List<Room> findAllByStatus(@Param("status") RoomStatusEnum status);

    // JOIN with partial fields — use Interface Projection
    @Query("SELECT r.name AS roomName, p.name AS playerName FROM Room r JOIN r.players p WHERE r.id = :id AND r.isDeleted = false")
    List<RoomPlayerView> findRoomWithPlayers(@Param("id") Long id);
}
```

### Interface Projection (preferred for JOIN queries)

Place projection interfaces in `dto/response/`. Hibernate fetches only the needed columns.

```java
// dto/response/RoomPlayerView.java
public interface RoomPlayerView {
    String getRoomName();
    String getPlayerName();
}
```

### DTO Projection (when result maps directly to an existing Response DTO)

```java
@Query("SELECT new com.prelude.randomz.dto.response.RoomPlayerResponse(r.name, p.name) " +
       "FROM Room r JOIN r.players p WHERE r.id = :id AND r.isDeleted = false")
List<RoomPlayerResponse> findRoomWithPlayersAsDto(@Param("id") Long id);
```

> Prefer **Interface Projection** for read-only JOIN queries.
> Use **DTO Projection** only when the result maps cleanly to an existing Response DTO and no further conversion is needed in the Service.

