## 8. Entity-to-DTO Mapping

**Never return an entity directly from Controller or Service.**
Always convert to a Response DTO before returning.

| Layer | Input | Output |
|---|---|---|
| Repository | — | `Entity` / `Projection` |
| ServiceImpl | `Entity` / `Projection` | `ResponseDTO` |
| Controller | `ResponseDTO` | `ApiResponse<ResponseDTO>` |

- Write a `private toResponse()` method in ServiceImpl to convert Entity → Response DTO.
- For `Page<Entity>`, use `.map(this::toResponse)`.
- Do **not** use MapStruct or other mapping libraries unless explicitly asked.

```java
private RoomResponse toResponse(Room room) {
    return new RoomResponse(
        room.getId(), room.getName(), room.getDescription(),
        room.getStatus(), room.getCurrentMode(),
        room.getStartTime(), room.getDuration()
    );
}
```

