## 11. Test Output (Pre-restart Handoff)

After passing the Section 10 checklist:

- Agent outputs a test plan containing **only the endpoints created or modified in this task**.
- Output the test to project .cursor/test-output folder, remember to clear to old output
Do not include endpoints that were not touched.

### Test plan format

```
## Test Plan

### {N}. {Label} — {METHOD} {path}
Body: {JSON payload}        ← omit if no body
Expect:
  - status: {expected status code}
  - {any specific field assertions}
```

### Examples by endpoint type

**Only POST /rooms was created:**
```
## Test Plan

### 1. Create — POST /api/v1/rooms
Body: { "name": "Test Room", "currentMode": "CLASSIC", "duration": 60 }
Expect:
  - status: 201
  - data.id is not null
  - data.name == "Test Room"

### 2. Validation Error — POST /api/v1/rooms
Body: {}
Expect:
  - status: 400
  - message contains "name"
```

**Only DELETE /rooms/{id} was created:**
```
## Test Plan

### 1. Delete — DELETE /api/v1/rooms/1
Expect:
  - status: 200
  - data == null

### 2. Confirm Soft Delete — GET /api/v1/rooms/1
Expect:
  - status: 404
```

**Multiple endpoints created:**
```
## Test Plan

### 1. Create — POST /api/v1/rooms
Body: { "name": "Test Room", "currentMode": "CLASSIC", "duration": 60 }
Expect:
  - status: 201
  - data.id is not null

### 2. Get By ID — GET /api/v1/rooms/{id from step 1}
Expect:
  - status: 200
  - data.id matches
```

> When steps depend on each other (e.g. GET uses id from POST),
> note the dependency explicitly as shown above.